een layers. Cover with cling wrap and let rise in a warm place for one hour or until doubled in size and dough springs back when touched. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 375°F."},{"content":"Once dough has risen in pan, bake for 35 minutes (375°F) until golden brown. Let cool 5 minutes in pan before inverting onto a serving plate. Serve warm with marinara sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To reheat Pizza Monkey Bread: place on a baking sheet and cover loosely with foil. Bake for 15-20 minutes (350°F) or until warmed through.","Use your oven's proofing feature or heat oven to 100°F and place dough inside to proof."],"basicInfo":["advanced","45m","2h 30m","27 pieces"]}